input.prompt:
Author a set of Blazor components for a checkout wizard using proper parameter passing and EventCallback patterns. Here are the models:

```csharp
public class ShippingInfo
{
    public string Name { get; set; } = "";
    public string Address { get; set; } = "";
    public string City { get; set; } = "";
    public string ZipCode { get; set; } = "";
}

public class PaymentInfo
{
    public string CardNumber { get; set; } = "";
    public string ExpiryDate { get; set; } = "";
}

public class Order
{
    public ShippingInfo Shipping { get; set; } = new();
    public PaymentInfo Payment { get; set; } = new();
}
```

Write the .razor component code for:
1. CheckoutWizard.razor — manages which step is active and holds the order state
2. ShippingStep.razor — collects shipping address fields, has a "Next" button. Name and Address must not be empty to proceed.
3. PaymentStep.razor — collects payment method, has "Back" and "Place Order" buttons

When "Place Order" is clicked, the parent of CheckoutWizard needs to receive the completed order via EventCallback.

